resource.chars: The M. E. G. Home Economics Club was organized in 1929 by the Senior
girls of the department. It was named for Miss Edna Groves, Supervisor of Home
Any Junior or Senior girl in the Home Economics Department, who wishes to
belong, may be a member. All Home Economics teachers, or faculty members who
have been former members of the Club, are welcomed to be members also.
Motto: Every Girl a Good Home- maker
